The 'Strategy RPG' tag on SteamDB is used to identify and categorize games that combine elements of both strategy and role-playing genres. Strategy RPGs typically involve turn-based combat systems, resource management, and character development through leveling up and skill trees. These games allow players to engage in tactical battles while also developing their characters' unique abilities and stories. Strategy RPGs may feature various gameplay mechanics, such as permadeath, morale systems, terrain effects, and complex quest lines. Players can explore expansive game worlds, build alliances, and make strategic decisions to influence the outcome of their campaigns. This tag helps users discover new games within this genre and compare them based on common features.
